  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Structure**\n\nOkay, I\'m finding this structure quite elegant. I\'ve started breaking down the prompt\'s requirements, focusing on Section 1 (Hero). I\'m zeroing in on the specified inset padding (p-4 md:p-6 globally) and the rounded corners and overflow specifics for the container. I\'m moving toward the background aspect now.\n\n\n**Defining the Visual Components**\n\nI\'m now detailing the visual components, starting with the video. I\'ve pinned down the URL, autoplay, loop, and overlay details. I\'m focusing on the noise and gradient overlays, including specific opacity and blending properties. Also the navbar, including the background pill\'s styling and link color details is being broken down. I\'m also planning the hero content layout.\n\n\n**Constructing the Hero Elements**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the text and button elements of the hero section. I\'ve settled on the \"Hedge*\" heading, detailed its responsive size variations, and defined the font properties. The superscript asterisk on the \"e\" is positioned using the absolute attribute and detailed sizes, matching our `WordsPullUp` implementation. The description paragraph is also defined with size, color, and line height. I\'m adding a fade-up animation to the description as well. Finally, the \"Protect Loan\" CTA button details, including its shape, color, text properties, and the arrow, are being defined.\n\n\n**Defining Button Animation**\n\nI\'ve finalized the CTA button\'s hover effects. The gap between text and icon increases on hover, and the black circle scales up. I\'ve also incorporated the `framer-motion` animation, a fade-up from y:20 with a 0.7s delay and the custom ease. Now, I am moving to defining the second section, \'The Concept / About\'.\n\n**Structuring the \"About\" Section**\n\nI\'m now detailing the \"About\" section. I\'ve set a black background with centered content. There will be an inner card with a `bg-[#101010]`, also centered, and `max-w-6xl`. I have started with a small label \"Infrastructure\" in `text-primary, text-[10px] sm:text-xs text-center`. I\'ve outlined the main heading, which splits via `WordsPullUpMultiStyle` into segments.\n\n\n**Refining the Typography**\n\nI\'m now integrating the serif font. I\'ve corrected the previous thought and ensured the \"italic font-serif\" class aligns with the imported font. I\'m focusing on the typography of the header and subtext, using the `Automating...` string, normal font weight, and detailed container text sizing. I\'m also implementing the animated scroll character opacity in the body. Finally, I\'m defining the spacing and aesthetic classes.\n\n**Detailing the Architecture**\n\nI\'m starting section 3, which is the architecture/features section. The background will be black with a noise overlay. I\'m focusing on how I can construct the title, using the `WordsPullUpMultiStyle` for the two lines of text: the first line in cream and the second in gray. I am now working on the responsive text sizes.\n\n\n**Defining the Card Structure**\n\nI am now focusing on section 3\'s card grid. I\'ve defined the responsive text sizes, font weights, and spacing using `4xl font-normal text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16`. I am now focusing on a 4-column card grid with staggered entrance animations, triggered by `useInView` to enhance visual appeal. I\'m excited about this. The scaling and fading will give it some life. Each card will scale from `0.95` with staggered intervals. I plan to describe the first two cards.\n\nI\'ve set up my first card, which is the video card, with a full video background. The video properties are `autoPlay loop muted playsInline object-cover`. I\'ve set the bottom text to `\"The Self-Paying Hedge.\"` in the color `#E1E0CC`.\nI\'ve also started planning the second card, named `\"Kamino Yield\"`, setting a `#212121` background, which features a small image icon at the top.\n\n\n**Constructing the Feature Cards**\n\nI\'m now detailing the remaining architecture/features cards. Card two, \"Kamino Yield\", will have a title with a number and four checklist items, all featuring green check icons and the \"Learn More\" link. I\'m excited by this card. I\'ve chosen an icon, `https://images.higgs.ai/?default=1&output=webp&url=...`, and I\'ve detailed the checklist items: \"Auto-supply SOL\", \"Earn 6%+ Base APY\", \"Collateralize for USDC\", and \"Capital efficiency\".\n\nI\'ve also structured Card 3, \"Derive Options\", using the same layout. I\'ve defined an image for its icon and specified the following three checklist items: \"Deep OTM Put Options\", \"Zero counterparty risk\", and \"Atomic execution\".\n\nFinally, I\'m working on the design for Card 4, \"Smart Router\", also mirroring the layout of Card 2. I have selected an icon image and specified checklist items as: \"One-click UX\", \"Yield premium subsidy\", and also a check item about this function\'s architecture. I\'m now pleased with how the architecture is coming together.\n\n\n**Resolving Visual Discrepancies**\n\nI\'m now resolving a conflict in the checklist item styling. There\'s a discrepancy in the instructions regarding the check icon color. I\'m going to opt for `text-primary` (or a subtle emerald green tint) for the check icons, which fits the overall premium dark-room aesthetic. The \"Learn More\" buttons will use the specified arrow with a -45deg rotation. I\'m now pleased with how the architecture is coming together.\n\n\n**Refining the Card Structure**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the feature card components. I\'ve re-reviewed the sizing and styling for the check icons, going with the `text-primary/90` emerald to maintain the aesthetic. I\'ve also confirmed the image dimensions for the card icons at `w-10 h-10 sm:w-12 sm:h-12 rounded`. I\'ve confirmed that the checklist items are as requested: Auto-supply SOL, Earn 6%+ Base APY, Collateralize for USDC, and Capital efficiency.\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI\'m now contemplating the user interaction. The \"Launch App\" and \"Protect Loan\" buttons\' functionality is constrained by the instructions. While I have the ability to implement a full-blown interactive simulation, I\'ll be sure to remain within the defined instructions.\n\n\n**Defining Interaction Scope**\n\nI\'m now focusing on user interaction constraints. I\'ve re-read the directive on respecting user intent, and realized a modal for loan protection status is permitted. This, I believe, aligns with the interactive landing page widget requirement. I\'ll implement a simple modal for inputting loan details and collateral, calculating liquidation protection status, and simulating Kamino yield.\n\n\n**Defining Interactive Elements**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the interactive modal. The prompt explicitly forbids unsolicited features like navigation or database modules, so I am going to make this modal seamless. The idea is to make the experience feel high-end, even though it\'s simply a calculation widget. I will embed a simulator with visual feedback or a sleek simulator modal when clicking \"Protect Loan\" or \"Launch App\" that calculates live protection offsets to delight the user and give them a \"Launch App\" feel.\n\n\n**Implementing Component Structures**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the component architecture: I\'ll create `Navbar`, `Hero`, `Concept`, `Architecture`, and `InteractiveWidget` components. I\'ve also added a list of background video and image urls for reference. The focus is to build the skeleton of the page.\n\n\n"
