  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Visual Design**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the visual architecture within Section 3. The foundational `min-h-screen bg-black` with the noise overlay is established. I\'m now examining the header text, utilizing `WordsPullUpMultiStyle` and its line structure.\n\n\n**Refining Card Animations**\n\nI\'ve been refining the staggered entrance animation for the 4-column card grid. Currently, each card scales from 0.95 and fades in using `useInView`, triggered once with a margin of -100px. I\'ve set the staggering at 0.15s intervals with an ease function of [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]. I\'m implementing variants for clean code, which will be mapped to indices.\n\n\n**Implementing Card Variants**\n\nI\'ve successfully integrated the animation variants into the card component, optimizing the code\'s readability and maintainability. The staggered entrance is working smoothly. I\'m now working on the individual card details, specifically the video card. I\'ve got the video background set, and I\'m adding bottom text to match design.\n\n\n**Designing Card Content**\n\nI\'m now focusing on structuring the content for the \"Kamino Yield\" card, aiming for a premium, terminal-like feel, similar to high-end fintech interfaces. I\'m implementing the title with its number, and designing the checklist with emerald-400 check icons and gray description text. I\'ve also added a \"Learn more\" link with the animated rotated arrow.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/Architecture.tsx` to handle Section 3, featuring a full background SVG noise texture, styled top segments, a 4-column balanced bento-grid, staggered scale and fade-in entries, checklist components with Check icons, and rotated Learn More links."
